  "prompt": "Which Chinese fighter aircraft is technologically most advanced and which US aircraft is comparable to it?",
  "response": "As of the latest developments, China's most technologically advanced fighter aircraft is the **Chengdu J-20 Mighty Dragon** (J-20). The J-20 is a fifth-generation stealth fighter designed for air superiority and precision strike missions. It features advanced stealth capabilities, sophisticated avionics, a modern Active Electronically Scanned Array (AESA) radar, and supercruise capability (the ability to fly at supersonic speeds without afterburners). The J-20 is often compared to Western fifth-generation fighters.\n\nThe most comparable U.S. aircraft to the J-20 is the **Lockheed Martin F-22 Raptor**. The F-22 is also a fifth-generation stealth fighter designed for air dominance. It has similar advanced features, including stealth technology, supercruise, and cutting-edge avionics. However, the F-22 has been in service since 2005 and is considered more mature in terms of operational experience, while the J-20 has entered service more recently and continues to evolve.\n\nAnother comparable aircraft is the **Lockheed Martin F-35 Lightning II**, though it is designed more as a multirole fighter with a focus on versatility, whereas the J-20 and F-22 are more focused on air superiority. \n\nIn summary, the **J-20** is China's most advanced fighter, and the **F-22 Raptor** is its closest U.S. counterpart in terms of role and technology.",
